  "_consistency_rule": "HARD ANCHORS: faces + height/age order (Maria ~13 tallest > Pepe ~12 > Luna ~9, small gaps, Luna not tiny). Outfits are ALWAYS stated explicitly in each panel prompt and default to the looks above; the model never improvises wardrobe. See CLAUDE.md for the reusable prompt header.",
  "_personality_note": "Personalities are story canon and stay consistent across ALL books. Recurring motifs are gentle, optional anchors — NOT required in every panel.",
  "_identity_lock": "Each character has a standardized reference (characters/refs/<name>_ref.png): same blue shirt, white bg, front pose. GOAL = consistent + clearly recognizable as that character, NOT photographic likeness. Attach refs to every prompt for face/hair consistency; lock hair, age order, outfits, personality. Chasing exact real-face likeness is explicitly NOT the target (it makes every panel a fight)."
